      <section eId="sec_3020">
        <num>3020</num>
        <heading>Sales of seized property</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_3020__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Any sale of property subject to\na tax lien must be sold at the fair market value of the property at the\ntime of the sale.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_3020__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The owner of any property seized by levy may request that the\ncommissioner sell such property within sixty days after the request (or\nwithin a longer period if specified by the owner). The commissioner\nshall comply with the request unless the commissioner determines (and\nnotifies the owner within such period) that such compliance would not be\nin the best interests of this state.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
